<h3><span class='material-icons'>radio</span><span><%= OPTS[:frequency] %>Mhz</h3>
<details>
<summary>HOW-TO</summary>

<details>
<summary>overview</summary>
<ul>
<li>radios allow the entire network to communicate in real time.</li>
<li>to use your radio, turn it on, press the button on the left and speak clearly.</li>
<li>extra batteries should always be carried.</li>
</ul>
</details>

<details>
<summary>rider</summary>
<ul>
<li>to call for others, send 'all stations <your username> <your message>'</li>
<li>to respond send '<other username> <your username> <your message>'</li>
<li>to listen to other channels, press the up or down arrows until you reach the appropriate channel.</li>
<li>to return to the main channel, press '001'</li>
</ul>
</details>

<details>
<summary>dispatch</summary>
<ul>
<li>relaying messages from the call center to the network is a very important job.</li>
<li>the call center will handle the job creation as calls come in.</li>
<li>jobs can be looked up and assigned accordingly.</li>
<li>payments should be managed before delivery if necessary.</li>
</ul>
</details>

<details>
<summary>admin</summary>
<ul>
<li>adding locations extends the network reach.</li>
<li>to add a new location to the network, visit the location, receive permissions and scan for location traffic, and take note of the location channel.</li>
<li>the channel will be added to the next radio update.</li>
</ul>
</details>

</details>